/------- Pseudocode 

for i → 0 to n - 2 do:
    min_idx → i

    for j → i + 1 to n - 1 do:
        if A[j] < A[min_idx] then
            min_idx → j

    if min_idx ≠ i then
        swap A[i] and min_idx]


/------- Algorithm 
 
1. Start
2. Input the number of elements n
3. Input the array A of size n
4. Repeat for i = 0 to n - 2:
    a. Set minIndex = i
    b. Repeat for j = i + 1 to n - 1:
        i. If A[j] < A[minIndex], then set minIndex = j
    c. If minIndex ≠ i, then swap A[i] and A[minIndex]


5. Output the sorted array